---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Zeton"
  description="Zeton is an original dark fantasy world in active development since 2023. 114 reference files, a complete magic system, geography, history, and a novel in progress."
>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow">

      <a href="/portfolio" class="back-link">&larr; Portfolio</a>

      <div class="project-header">
        <span class="item-tag">Creative &middot; Worldbuilding &middot; Work in progress</span>
        <h1>Zeton</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="project-body">
        <p class="project-lead">
          An original dark fantasy world in active development since 2023.
          Not adapted from existing fiction, not borrowing established lore.
          Built from the ground up - designed to support a novel. Possibly more.
        </p>

        <p>
          The world exists independently of any story. Mythology, geography, history,
          language, and magic were all developed before a word of the novel was written -
          so that when the writing happens, the world underneath it doesn't give way.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-heading">What exists</h2>

        <p>
          The vault currently holds 114 documented reference files across 17+ categories.
          Everything listed below is complete enough to be written against today.
        </p>

        <ul class="vault-list">
          <li>
            <strong>History</strong>
            Multiple distinct eras spanning thousands of in-world years, each with its own
            civilisational character and dedicated documentation.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Geography</strong>
            A fully documented central city of approximately 500,000 residents, built down to
            justice systems, food supply, trade routes, economy, and social structure. Three
            outer cities with distinct identities and economies. A frontier territory. A
            world-ocean with documented unusual properties.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Magic system</strong>
            Eight individual ability types, each with its own cost mechanics. Five universal
            governing laws. Sub-systems covering progression, corruption, environmental
            interaction, and combination mechanics. A three-tier taxonomy of practitioners.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Calendar and cosmology</strong>
            A dual-moon lunar cycle. A 343-day year divided into seven named seasons. A
            recurring astronomical event with major civic significance, documented in full.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Weather</strong>
            Eleven-plus named meteorological phenomena, split between ordinary and
            magic-influenced categories. Each has its own documented mechanics.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Language</strong>
            A constructed naming system with phonetic rules, a continuously updated etymology
            registry, and dedicated root vocabulary files.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Governance</strong>
            Four civic institutions with distinct charters. Three governing bodies with defined
            jurisdictional relationships. A five-tier licensing system.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Additional</strong>
            Weapons, technology, entities, flora and fauna, and historical persons - all
            documented at varying depth.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          The vault functions as a reference system, not a collection of notes. Where content
          hasn't been formally detailed yet, placeholders mark what logically must exist.
          The world is designed to be larger than its documentation at every stage.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-heading">The novel</h2>

        <p>
          Genre: Dark Fantasy, with Mythological Fantasy and Psychological Fantasy as
          secondary registers.
        </p>

        <p>
          Mythology shapes the structural bones of the world - not just the aesthetics.
          Psychology is treated as terrain: the inner lives of characters carry the same
          weight as anything external. A rough outline exists. Several chapter drafts have
          been written. No completed manuscript yet.
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="/portfolio/blind-tracks">Blind Tracks</a> is a short story set inside
          this world - written to test whether the internal logic held under narrative
          pressure. It placed third in the UCY Literary Competition 2026.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-heading">How it's built</h2>

        <p>The methodology is as deliberate as the content.</p>

        <ul class="method-list">
          <li>
            <strong>Author-truth vs. in-world knowledge</strong> is maintained as a formal
            distinction throughout every file. Many of the world's most important mechanics
            are unknown to the people living inside it. The vault tracks what is true
            separately from what is known - and mixing them is treated as a world-breaking
            error.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Etymology as a standing constraint.</strong> Every new term coined for
            the world must fit its phonetic rules and be logged in the etymology registry
            before the session closes. The constructed vocabulary isn't decorative - it
            governs what names are even possible.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Continuous review.</strong> New canon triggers a check of all existing
            files for inconsistency or staleness. The world is treated as a single coherent
            system where new facts have downstream consequences that must be tracked.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>AI for consistency, not content.</strong> AI is used to flag logical
            contradictions across the vault when asked - nothing more. No content is
            AI-generated. Every idea, decision, and direction is mine. This is a personal
            line, not a technical one - this world matters too much to me to hand any
            part of it over.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="wip-note">
          <span class="wip-label">Status</span>
          <p>Active development since 2023. Rough outline complete. Chapter drafts written.
          No completed manuscript yet.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider" />

      <div class="project-footer">
        <a href="/portfolio" class="btn btn--ghost">&larr; Back to portfolio</a>
        <a href="/portfolio/blind-tracks" class="btn btn--ghost">Read Blind Tracks &rarr;</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .project-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .item-tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  h1 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .project-body {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .project-lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--color-text);
    max-width: 58ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .project-body p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: clamp(1.375rem, 2.5vw, 1.75rem);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  /* Vault list - category breakdown */
  .vault-list,
  .method-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg) 0;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }

  .vault-list li,
  .method-list li {
    padding: var(--space-md) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .vault-list li:last-child,
  .method-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .vault-list strong,
  .method-list strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .wip-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
  }

  .wip-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .wip-note p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 55ch;
  }

  .project-footer {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
</style>
